Hey!  Wharf Rat.. if you want to rescue Richard the Rodent, then help yourself.  I hate rats, remember.  Is he a man or a mouse?  Why does he need Daddy Rat to do his squeaking?<br>
If I give an apology it will be to those who suffer because of their service to their country... certainly not those who continue to mask their shame for being cowards.<br>
To me, the only valid war protestor is the man who hates the filth, horror, death and destruction of war as he crawls or limps off the battlefield.  Parents, wives, children, and friends of the deceased and surviving servants have license to protest... for they too have sacrificed.  All humanity should protest war.<br>
My respect goes to the person who protested the war while dodging bullets... not dodging the draft.  My respect goes to the man who tells me that he is sorry that he did not serve in Viet Nam.  My response is, &quot;I'm glad that you didn't have to go.&quot;<br>
I will apologize to Richard when he asks forgiveness for being a traitor.  I will clench my teeth and try to accept him as a man needing internalized truths and character and perhaps share with him some of mine.  Until then, I view you and him with contempt and disgust... and do not wish to argue the merits of virture with a pair of political whores. <br><br>
Mustang Two Four<br><br>
P.S.  My name is Edward.  My deceased brother's name is Edmond.  He died as a result of his service to the 11th Armored Cavalry Regiment in 1968. 
